section.section:
The Board shall develop a master plan document that sets forth in detail all of the terms and conditions of the standard benefit package required by subsection (a)(1) of this section, including:
the benefits provided in the package;
any exclusions from coverage;
any conditions requiring preauthorizations or utilization review as a condition to obtaining a benefit or service;
any conditions or limitations on the selection of a primary care provider or provider of specialty medical care;
any cost-sharing requirements, including any premiums, deductibles, coinsurance, and copayment amounts for which a member may be responsible; and
the procedures to be followed in presenting a claim.

text.section:
The Board may make a change to the standard benefit package only if:
the proposed change is submitted in writing to the Board at least 15 days before the meeting at which a vote on the proposed change will be taken;
consideration of the proposed change is listed as an action item on the agenda for the meeting;
the proposed change is set forth in a written motion that:
identifies the specific changes to be made; and
is included in the minutes of the meeting of the Board at which the motion is made;
the deliberations and vote on the proposed change occur during a public session of a meeting with the Board; and
the vote approving the proposed change is reflected in the minutes of the meeting of the Board at which the vote is taken.
